250 g Ground Beef
28 g Croutons
20 g Gravy Spice Blend
113 g Mushrooms
56 g Onion, sliced
56 g Kale, chopped
7 g Dill
43 mL Sour Cream
21.5 mL Creamy Dressing
7.5 g Beef Stock Powder
6 g Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Heat a large pot over medium-high.
Meanwhile, thinly slice mushrooms into 1/4-inch slices.
When the pot is hot, add beef, mushrooms and onions to the dry pot. Cook for 5-6 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.

Add Gravy Spice Blend, Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and half the creamy dressing (use all for 4 servings). Cook for 30 sec, scraping up any brown bits from the bottom of the pan.
Add 2 1/2 cups (5 cups) water and stock powder, then bring up to a simmer.

Once soup is simmering, add kale and cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally, until kale wilts slightly. Season with salt and pepper.

Remove soup from heat.
Divide soup between bowls.
Top with sour cream and croutons.
Snip dill over top.